# Data Layer

## Supabase — server only

```typescript
// ❌ NEVER in client components or 'use client' files
import { createClient } from '@/lib/supabase/server'

// ✅ API route or Server Component only
const supabase = await createClient()
```

- Types: always from `types/supabase.ts` (generated).
- Frontend field names MUST match Supabase column names.

## Layer separation

```
app/api/[resource]/route.ts   → thin handler (validate + call service)
lib/services/[resource].ts    → all Supabase queries & business logic
lib/api/client.ts             → generic fetch wrapper (client-side, for React Query)
```

API route example:

```typescript
// app/api/users/route.ts
export async function GET() {
  const data = await getUsers() // from lib/services/users.ts
  return NextResponse.json(data)
}
```

Service reusable in both API routes AND Server Components:

```typescript
// lib/services/users.ts
export async function getUsers() { /* supabase query */ }
```

## Generic fetch client

All client-side API calls go through `lib/api/client.ts` — never raw `fetch()` scattered in components.

```typescript
// lib/api/client.ts
export async function apiClient<T>(path: string, options?: RequestInit): Promise<T>
```

## API response shape

Consistent JSON responses:

```typescript
// success: { data: T }
// error:   { error: string, code?: string }
```
